sheTssmMib.name: sheTssmMib

revisions.description: Change sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucChanInterleaveMinTxRate to sheTssmLastLinkUpLogConfiguredRateDown; Change sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturChanInterleaveMinTxRate to sheTssmLastLinkUpLogConfiguredRateUp; Remove the sheTssmProfileTable, move all TSSM configurations to sheTssmPortTable. sheTssmPortControl group was changed accordingly.
According to the newest TSSM standard, a new variable sheTssmMissTargetRateCriteria was added into the object list of traps sheTssmMissTargetRateTrap and sheTssmReachTargetRateTrap.
Bring them to common SHE MIB package with R2.8.

sheTssmMib.contactinfo: COO BBA Siemens Building in Beijing jie.shen@nsn.com ###################### gerd.barchmann@nsn.com
sheTssmMib.description: The MIB module describes managed objects that support Training Speed Statistical Monitoring (TSSM) feature.

sheTssmFtpRootDir.name: sheTssmFtpRootDir
sheTssmFtpRootDir.description: The root directory name on FTP server that stores the TSSM data of this DSLAM. It is the relative path to the ftproot, eg. 'hix5635/v1.5/dslam1/tssm' The directory structure looks like: ftproot <-- the upmost ftp root |- %FtpRootDir% <-- this value, specifies the DSLAM

sheTssmFtpUser.name: sheTssmFtpUser
sheTssmFtpUser.description: FTP user name. Write permission is required for this user.

sheTssmFtpPassword.name: sheTssmFtpPassword
sheTssmFtpPassword.description: FTP server access password. To protect the password, the string of this object in the GetResponse PDU is encrypted.

sheTssmUploadInterval.name: sheTssmUploadInterval
sheTssmUploadInterval.description: The interval that TSSM data is uploaded to FTP server. It increases with step of 1 hour.

sheTssmUploadEnabled.name: sheTssmUploadEnabled
sheTssmUploadEnabled.description: Whether the NE should upload the log files to FTP server.

sheTssmLogEnabled.name: sheTssmLogEnabled
sheTssmLogEnabled.description: Whether the NE should keep the log of link parameters.

sheTssmMissTargetRateCriteria.name: sheTssmMissTargetRateCriteria
sheTssmMissTargetRateCriteria.description: The criteria of when the miss tartget rate trap should be sent.

sheTssmControlRequest.name: sheTssmControlRequest
sheTssmControlRequest.description: Command (setTssmGlobalParameters) to configure the global TSSM parameters. It must be the last member in the varBindList of the SNMP set request. The parameters of this command are: sheTssmControlFtpRootDir sheTssmControlFtpIp sheTssmControlFtpUser sheTssmControlFtpPassword sheTssmControlUploadInterval sheTssmControlUploadEnabled sheTssmControlLogEnabled sheTssmControlMissTargetRateCriteria They are optional in the varBindList of set PDU, but at least one of them should be there. Notifications: sheTssmControlResult at the command ending in case of long running command. The long running command refers to the case that sheTssmUploadEnabled is changed from disable to enable. NE will verify the FTP connection at the enabling moment. Besides, the RootDir is created if it does not exist yet. EM should GET sheTssmControlReqResult when the Response of the SET PDU is received, and the error status is noError. If the value of sheTssmControlReqResult is comExecStarted(30), which means the SET operation is a long running command, EM must issue another GET operation on sheTssmControlTimer. A timer should start on EM with the expire time equals to the value of sheTssmControlTimer. The sheTssmControlResult trap is expected to reach EM within the specified time. When the trap is received by EM, EM can optionally GET sheTssmControlReqResult, sheTssmControlStatus, and sheTssmControlTimeStamp.

sheTssmControlStatus.name: sheTssmControlStatus
sheTssmControlStatus.description: The status of a control request.

sheTssmControlTimer.name: sheTssmControlTimer
sheTssmControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for command ending. For long running commands. The manager reads this value from the SHE.

sheTssmControlReqResult.name: sheTssmControlReqResult
sheTssmControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheTssmControlTimeStamp.name: sheTssmControlTimeStamp
sheTssmControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheTssmControlFtpRootDir.name: sheTssmControlFtpRootDir
sheTssmControlFtpRootDir.description: The root directory name on FTP server that stores the TSSM data of this DSLAM. Change the value of sheTssmFtpRootDir.

sheTssmControlFtpIp.name: sheTssmControlFtpIp
sheTssmControlFtpIp.description: FTP server's IP address. Change the value of sheTssmFtpIp.

sheTssmControlFtpUser.name: sheTssmControlFtpUser
sheTssmControlFtpUser.description: FTP user name. Change the value of sheTssmFtpUser.

sheTssmControlFtpPassword.name: sheTssmControlFtpPassword
sheTssmControlFtpPassword.description: FTP server access password. To protect the password, the string of this object in the GetResponse PDU is encrypted.

sheTssmControlUploadInterval.name: sheTssmControlUploadInterval
sheTssmControlUploadInterval.description: The interval that TSSM data is uploaded to FTP server. Change the value of sheTssmUploadInterval.

sheTssmControlUploadEnabled.name: sheTssmControlUploadEnabled
sheTssmControlUploadEnabled.description: Whether the FTP upload process is enabled. Change the value of sheTssmUploadEnabled. If the sheTssmUploadEnabled is changed from disable to enable, FTP connection will be verified at the enabling moment. Besides, the RootDir is created if it does not exist yet. The command in this case is a long running command. sheTssmControlResult trap will be sent to EM to notify the command result.

sheTssmControlLogEnabled.name: sheTssmControlLogEnabled
sheTssmControlLogEnabled.description: Whether the NE should keep the log of link parameters. Change the value of sheTssmLogEnabled.

sheTssmControlMissTargetRateCriteria.name: sheTssmControlMissTargetRateCriteria
sheTssmControlMissTargetRateCriteria.description: The criteria of when the miss tartget rate trap should be sent.

sheTssmLastUploadStatus.name: sheTssmLastUploadStatus
sheTssmLastUploadStatus.description: The status of last FTP upload operation. It could be uploadSuccess(1) or uploadFail(2).

sheTssmLastUploadTimeStamp.name: sheTssmLastUploadTimeStamp
sheTssmLastUploadTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last FTP upload operation (end of operation).

sheTssmLastUploadFileName.name: sheTssmLastUploadFileName
sheTssmLastUploadFileName.description: The file name of last FTP upload operation.

sheTssmLastUploadErrorString.name: sheTssmLastUploadErrorString
sheTssmLastUploadErrorString.description: The text that describes the FTP upload failure. If upload succeeded, this string is empty.

sheTssmPortTable.name: sheTssmPortTable
sheTssmPortTable.description: This table contains configuration parameters for TSSM on each ADSL port.

sheTssmPortTrapEnabled.name: sheTssmPortTrapEnabled
sheTssmPortTrapEnabled.description: Indicates whether this ADSL port is allowed to send trap to EM. If the stable trained rate on this line is lower than the configured threshold, sheTssmMissTargetRateTrap will be sent to alarm EM. If at next linkup, the stable trained rate is higher than the configured threshold, another trap (sheTssmReachTargetRateTrap) will be sent to clear the last alarm.

sheTssmPortThresholdUnit.name: sheTssmPortThresholdUnit
sheTssmPortThresholdUnit.description: Indicates what type of unit (kbps or percentage)is used to configure the TSSM threshold.

sheTssmPortThresholdRateDownKbps.name: sheTssmPortThresholdRateDownKbps
sheTssmPortThresholdRateDownKbps.description: The configured threshold of downstream transmit rate on the channel. It is used only if sheTssmPortThresholdUnit is set to kbps(1).

sheTssmPortThresholdRateUpKbps.name: sheTssmPortThresholdRateUpKbps
sheTssmPortThresholdRateUpKbps.description: The configured threshold of upstream transmit rate on the channel. It is used only if sheTssmPortThresholdUnit is set to kbps(1).

sheTssmPortThresholdRateDownRatio.name: sheTssmPortThresholdRateDownRatio
sheTssmPortThresholdRateDownRatio.description: The configured threshold of downstream transmit rate on the channel. It is used only if sheTssmPortThresholdUnit is set to percentage(2).

sheTssmPortThresholdRateUpRatio.name: sheTssmPortThresholdRateUpRatio
sheTssmPortThresholdRateUpRatio.description: The configured threshold of upstream transmit rate on the channel. It is used only if sheTssmPortThresholdUnit is set to percentage(2).

sheTssmPortControlRequest.name: sheTssmPortControlRequest
sheTssmPortControlRequest.description: Command to configure sheTssmPortTable (setTssmPortParameters). It must be the last member in the varBindList of the SNMP set request. The parameters of this command are: (must) sheTssmPortControlType sheTssmPortControlRange (the following parameters depend on the value of above two parameters) sheTssmPortControlIndex sheTssmPortControlTrapEnabled sheTssmPortControlThresholdUnit sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateDownKbps sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateUpKbps sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateDownRatio sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateUpRatio

sheTssmPortControlStatus.name: sheTssmPortControlStatus
sheTssmPortControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

sheTssmPortControlTimer.name: sheTssmPortControlTimer
sheTssmPortControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheTssmPortControlReqResult.name: sheTssmPortControlReqResult
sheTssmPortControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheTssmPortControlTimeStamp.name: sheTssmPortControlTimeStamp
sheTssmPortControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheTssmPortControlType.name: sheTssmPortControlType
sheTssmPortControlType.description: Indicates what parameters are configured in this command. It can be: configAlarmOnly(1): Only sheTssmPortControlTrapEnabled is configured to the specified ports. The threshold parametes are ignored. configThresholdOnly(2): Only configure the threshold parameters to specified ports. sheTssmPortControlTrapEnabled is ignored. configBoth(3): Configure both type of parameters.

sheTssmPortControlRange.name: sheTssmPortControlRange
sheTssmPortControlRange.description: Indicates how to configure the TSSM parameters to ports. It can be: system(1): apply the parameters to all the ports in the whole DSLAM module(2): apply the parameters to all the ports on a module (board) port(3): apply the parameters to a specific port.

sheTssmPortControlIndex.name: sheTssmPortControlIndex
sheTssmPortControlIndex.description: Depends on the value of sheTssmPortControlRange, this object has different meaning: sheTssmPortControlRange sheTssmPortControlIndex ----------------------- ----------------------- system(1) N/A module(2) the entPhysIndex of card port(3) IfIndex of the configured adsl-interface

sheTssmPortControlTrapEnabled.name: sheTssmPortControlTrapEnabled
sheTssmPortControlTrapEnabled.description: Indicates whether the specified ADSL port is allowed to send trap to EM. If the stable trained rate on this line is lower than the configured threshold, a trap will be sent to alarm EM. If at next linkup, the stable trained rate is higher than the configured threshold, another trap will be sent to clear the last alarm.

sheTssmPortControlThresholdUnit.name: sheTssmPortControlThresholdUnit
sheTssmPortControlThresholdUnit.description: Indicates what type of unit is used to configure the TSSM threshold. It can be kbps(1), or percentage(2)

sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateDownKbps.name: sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateDownKbps
sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateDownKbps.description: The configured threshold of downstream transmit rate on the channel. It is used only if sheTssmPortThresholdUnit is set to kbps(1).

sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateUpKbps.name: sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateUpKbps
sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateUpKbps.description: The configured threshold of upstream transmit rate on the channel. It is used only if sheTssmPortThresholdUnit is set to kbps(1).

sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateDownRatio.name: sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateDownRatio
sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateDownRatio.description: The configured threshold of downstream transmit rate on the channel. It is used only if sheTssmPortThresholdUnit is set to percentage(2).

sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateUpRatio.name: sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateUpRatio
sheTssmPortControlThresholdRateUpRatio.description: The configured threshold of upstream transmit rate on the channel. It is used only if sheTssmPortThresholdUnit is set to percentage(2).

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogTable.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogTable
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogTable.description: Each entry in this table contains the ADSL line parameters of a port for last link up.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogLinkTime.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogLinkTime
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogLinkTime.description: The time when the link up happened last time on this port.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucTxRate.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucTxRate
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucTxRate.description: The stable downstream transmit rate on the channel. It is the value of sheAdslAtucChanCurrTxRate when the link up is stable.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturTxRate.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturTxRate
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturTxRate.description: The stable upstream transmit rate on the channel. It is the value of sheAdslAturChanCurrTxRate when the link up is stable.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucSnrMgn.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucSnrMgn
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucSnrMgn.description: Noise Margin as seen by this ATU with respect to its received signal in tenth dB. It is the value of sheAdslAtucPhysCurrSnrMgn when the link up is stable.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturSnrMgn.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturSnrMgn
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturSnrMgn.description: Noise Margin as seen by this ATU with respect to its received signal in tenth dB. It is the value of sheAdslAturPhysCurrSnrMgn when the link up is stable.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucAtn.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucAtn
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucAtn.description: Measured difference in the total power transmitted by the peer ATU and the total power received by this ATU. It is the value of sheAdslAtucPhysCurrAtn when the link up is stable.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturAtn.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturAtn
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturAtn.description: Measured difference in the total power transmitted by the peer ATU and the total power received by this ATU. It is the value of sheAdslAturPhysCurrAtn when the link up is stable.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucAttainableRate.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucAttainableRate
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucAttainableRate.description: Indicates the maximum attainable data rate by the ATU. It is the value of sheAdslAtucPhysCurrAttainableRate when the link up is stable.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturAttainableRate.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturAttainableRate
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturAttainableRate.description: Indicates the maximum attainable data rate by the ATU. It is the value of sheAdslAturPhysCurrAttainableRate when the link up is stable.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucTxRateThreshold.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucTxRateThreshold
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucTxRateThreshold.description: The configured threshold of downstream transmit rate on the channel.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturTxRateThreshold.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturTxRateThreshold
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturTxRateThreshold.description: The configured threshold of upstream transmit rate on the channel.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucChanInterleaveDe.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucChanInterleaveDelay
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucChanInterleaveDe.description: Interleave Delay for this channel. It is the value of sheAdslAtucChanInterleaveDelay when the link up is stable.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturChanInterleaveDe.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturChanInterleaveDelay
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturChanInterleaveDe.description: Interleave Delay for this channel. It is the value of sheAdslAturChanInterleaveDelay when the link up is stable.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucTargetSnrMgn.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucTargetSnrMgn
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAtucTargetSnrMgn.description: Configured Target Signal/Noise Margin on this line. It is the value of sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucConfTargetSnrMgn when the link up is stable.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturTargetSnrMgn.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturTargetSnrMgn
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogAturTargetSnrMgn.description: Configured Target Signal/Noise Margin on this line. It is the value of sheAdslLineConfProfileAturConfTargetSnrMgn when the link up is stable.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogConfiguredRateDown.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogConfiguredRateDown
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogConfiguredRateDown.description: Configured downstream transmit rate for the channel on this line, in kbps. It is the value of sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucChanConfFastMaxTxRate or sheAdslLineConfProfileAtucChanConfInterleaveMaxTxRate, depending on the mode of the channel is fast or interleave.

sheTssmLastLinkUpLogConfiguredRateUp.name: sheTssmLastLinkUpLogConfiguredRateUp
sheTssmLastLinkUpLogConfiguredRateUp.description: Configured upstream transmit rate for the channel on this line, in kbps. It is the value of sheAdslLineConfProfileAturChanConfFastMaxTxRate or sheAdslLineConfProfileAturChanConfInterleaveMaxTxRate, depending on the mode of the channel is fast or interleave.

sheTssmLastLinkDownLogTable.name: sheTssmLastLinkDownLogTable
sheTssmLastLinkDownLogTable.description: Each entry in this table contains the ADSL line parameters of a port for last link down.

sheTssmLastLinkDownLogLinkTime.name: sheTssmLastLinkDownLogLinkTime
sheTssmLastLinkDownLogLinkTime.description: The time when the link down happened last time on this port.

sheTssmControlResult.name: sheTssmControlResult
sheTssmControlResult.description: Notification sent at the end of long running command. The possible values of sheTssmControlReqResult are: wrongIpAddress(2), -- IP address of FTP servre is incorrect wrongUserPassword(3), -- The user name or password is wrong permissionDenied(4), -- The user name has no permission to create dir/file commandSucceeded(37)

sheTssmUploadFailedTrap.name: sheTssmUploadFailedTrap
sheTssmUploadFailedTrap.description: Indicates that an FTP upload failure occurred.

sheTssmMissTargetRateTrap.name: sheTssmMissTargetRateTrap
sheTssmMissTargetRateTrap.description: Indicates that the stable link rate does not meet the target rate on the ADSL port specified by ifIndex. The EM will show an alarm on this port. The corresponding parameters are included in the trap.

sheTssmReachTargetRateTrap.name: sheTssmReachTargetRateTrap
sheTssmReachTargetRateTrap.description: If at last time, the ADSL port that specified by ifIndex missed the target rate, and the sheTssmMissTargetRateTrap was sent, but it met the target rate at this link up, this trap is sent. The EM can clear the alarm then. The corresponding parameters are included in the trap.
